	issn = {1877-0509},
	url = {https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1877050925024354},
	doi = {10.1016/j.procs.2025.08.124},
	abstract = {This paper proposes a multi-view machine learning framework for predicting audit opinions by integrating structured financial metrics and numerically extracted semantic indicators from annual disclosures. Both views are derived from the authoritative CN-RDS platform, with the first capturing traditional quantitative indicators and the second comprising linguistic features computed from audit-related texts. A unified dataset is constructed to align these complementary modalities, enabling a holistic representation of corporate reporting. To effectively fuse heterogeneous information, we design a Multi-View Neural Network (MVNN) with view-specific encoders and an element-wise max-pooling fusion mechanism to capture cross-view dependencies. Besides, we incorporate the focal loss to handle the class imbalance issue. Empirical evaluations demonstrate that the proposed model consistently outperforms single-view baselines. Our findings highlight that integrating multiple data views can significantly improve the performance of audit opinion prediction and provide actionable guidance for more informed and data-driven assurance decisions.},
